title: For Sale:  Miniature Revolver
postcontent:
Xythos Automatic. The world's smallest working revolver. This six shot double action revolver is about the size of a quarter. Made in Austria from 1960 to 1980. It fires 2mm pinfire blanks.

The frame is nickel plated with black plastic grips. The revolving cylinder has six chambers for the 2mm pinfire blanks and an blanked chamber. Always keep the hammer on an empty chamber for safety. Once loaded simply pull the trigger and the hammer cocks then fires, bang, bang, bang. . . just like its bigger counter parts made by Colt, Smith & Wesson, Ruger or Taurus.

When the left grip panel is removed there is a compartment that allows for the attachment of a key chain. Also on the left side of the frame is a screw that when removed allows the attachment of either a mushroom shaped post or a tie bar allowing the revolver to be worn as a cuff link or tie clasp. Each revolver comes in a fitted plastic case with all accessories and instructions.

I have four of these revolvers. A single unit with the cuff link attachment in the round case and a set of three, two round cases with cuff links and one square case with the tie bar. The single unit comes with 6 rounds of blank cartridges and the 3 piece set includes 36 rounds in the original red cartridge box. All four revolvers are in like new unfired condition. Perfect for any gun collector or miniatures collector.

Single unit $185 3 piece set $525

Though not classified as firearms by the BATFE, these are not toy guns. They should be treated with the same respect and eye towards safety one would use with their larger .38 Special, .357 Magnum or 44 Mag brethren.

Ruger Old Army .45 Caliber 

The Ruger Old Army is a black-powder percussion revolver produced in 1972-2008 (the stainless model - in 1975-2008). It wasn't based on a historical design but was a modification of Ruger Blackhawk although it takes its styling cues from the Remington 1858 New Army. 

The Ruger Old Army is designed to be the most advanced and accurate cap and ball revolver ever made. It features an innovative hammer and base pin assembly that will not come open during recoil and can be disassembled without tools for quick and easy cleaning and maintenance, even at the range. This revolver has a round barrel, stainless steel frame, 6-shot cylinder, fully adjustable target type sights and 2-piece grips

The Old Army is stainless steel, with fully adjustable target-type sights, and a 7.5" barrel.
